.change.org/u/1020134"},{"created_at":"2013-07-22T15:08:08Z","content":"She should be given a promotion!  She's clearly thinking and acting responsibly!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hollis Dolben","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/593659"},{"created_at":"2013-07-17T02:59:48Z","content":"I really think we need more people to speak for the animals they have no voice and thank god Carla did. The manager should be fired for listening to an idiot complain about her ,,,he should not have left his dog in the car if he cared about his dog.\r\nI won't even go in Walmart now and shop there.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda Martinig","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56711273"},{"created_at":"2013-07-17T02:48:33Z","content":"Right is right and sorry Walmart your wrong to fire anyone for doing the right thing.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michael Brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56709331"},{"created_at":"2013-07-16T02:48:50Z","content":"This was a clear cut case of animal cruelty. Get your act together walmart.","like_count":0,"author_name":"marc desaulniers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26617896"},{"created_at":"2013-07-15T16:02:30Z","content":"The actions of the management of Walmart, Kemptville are contemptible.  Dogs and children are being left in cars by their owners/parents to fry while those people shop or go to bars.  Just look at the number of incidents this year alone.  Ms. Cheney, on her own time, took an action that is worthy of accolades.  Instead, the neanderthal who runs your store stripped her of her means of making a living.  I will NOT shop at your stores until I see a reversal of this miscarriage of justice by someone on a power trip.  As you are aware, this incident has gone viral.  We are watching!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kathleen Schaper","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56561568"},{"created_at":"2013-07-14T19:37:15Z","content":"Animals are family members and the one or two people that get upset because they are breaking laws and leaving their family member but not to them its just a pet in the car should not matter. What matters is the person that looked beyond their own concerns to help another being and will be supported in their decision my the community but obviously not by her employer. If I was her employer I would be saying thank you for thinking of safety and well being which I thought was a huge part of walmarts policies.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Teri Moore","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/54981164"},{"created_at":"2013-07-14T17:31:50Z","content":"She ABSOLUTELY did the right thing. A life is a life whether it is animal or human. She deserves commendation from Walmart not job loss. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carol Breakell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56019014"},{"created_at":"2013-07-14T16:11:07Z","content":"If Carla called the police because a child was left in that car without the windows open, she'd be commended. But she's fired because instead of a child it's a dog. Real nice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ari Herzog","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56464946"},{"created_at":"2013-07-14T15:06:46Z","content":"Cruelty to animals becoming cruelty to people.  Seriously? ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tony Di Giovanni","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56460974"},{"created_at":"2013-07-14T12:41:01Z","content":"Being fired over saving an animals life is 100% wrong! When are retail companies are going to stand up to the rude customers instead of bending over backwards?  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elaine Hemingway","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56453175"},{"created_at":"2013-07-14T11:24:48Z","content":"The customer is NOT always right. Please reinstate this woman immediately.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rose Brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30773587"},{"created_at":"2013-07-14T03:49:05Z","content":"It's against the law to leave an animal in a hot car, what Carla did was the right thing. Give her job back, or this customer will not shop at walmart until you give her, her job back..","like_count":0,"author_name":"Teresa Pitts","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6292960"},{"created_at":"2013-07-14T01:35:10Z","content":"Pet ownership is a responsibility.  Death by ignorance is no excuse.\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michael Fisher","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56428425"},{"created_at":"2013-07-13T21:42:49Z","content":"Because it's setting a dangerous precedent in letting employees come forward to report something they feel strongly about.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Danny Brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/dannybrown"}]}
